definitions.definition: ( impersonal pronoun , indefinite ) One thing (among a group of others); one member of a group.
examples: Every one of the bank’s employees.
A good driver is one who drives carefully.
Can I borrow an eraser? — Sorry pal, I haven't got one .
He's not one to pull his punches.

definitions.definition: ( impersonal pronoun , sometimes with "the" ) The first mentioned of two things or people, as opposed to the other .
examples: She offered him an apple and an orange; he took (the) one and left the other.
I am one of the few women who've climbed Everest.

definitions.definition: ( indefinite personal pronoun ) Any person (applying to people in general).
examples: One’s guilt may trouble one , but it is best not to let oneself be troubled by things which cannot be changed. One shouldn’t be too quick to judge.
My neighbor talks to one like a teacher.

definitions.definition: ( pronoun ) Any person , entity or thing .
